         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">27th July [187]0 ¶ Sir, ¶  ¶ The committee of management of the above Museum direct me to express to you their marked satisfaction at the able manner in which you have and are conducting the classifyi...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">70.07.27d</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Marcus Clarke</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Letter no. 20/I.T.M., Outward letterbook 1870-9 p. 11, Industrial and Technological Museum and Public Library, Museum Victoria.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">27th July [187]0<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">editorial addition.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Sir,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The committee of management of the above Museum direct me to express to you their marked satisfaction at the able manner in which you have and are conducting the classifying and labelling of specimens for your section of the Industrial Museum exhibition, but require me to suggest to you that as the Museum is intended to be a popular institution as well as a scientific collection, it would in their opinion be advisable to place the <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">English</hi>
               </seg> and <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">common</hi>
               </seg>, as well as the <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">scientific</hi>
               </seg> and <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Latin</hi>
               </seg> names on the wood specimens you have so elegantly and admirably arranged</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">I have the honor to be</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Sir</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Your obedient Servant</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Marcus Clarke<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>For reply, see M to M. Clarke, 27 July 1870 (in this edition as 70-07-27b).</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Dr Von Mueller.</p>
